rd - privilege elevator
=======================
rd is a privilege elevation tool. It takes in the root password each time it is
run and will reject an incorrect login attempt or run a command.

Requirements
------------
In order to build rd, you need the crypt header file. rd is build for the Linux
model of group and password storage; it will not work on other types of systems.

Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup.

Afterwards, enter the following command to build and install rd (if necessary,
as root):

    make clean install

